# Social Media Do's and Don'ts for College Students

---

## ✅ DO's

| # | Do's |
|---|------|
| 1 | Do keep your profiles professional – Use a clear profile picture and ensure your bio reflects your academic/professional interests. |
| 2 | Do think before you post – Ask yourself: "Would I be comfortable if a professor or employer saw this?" before hitting publish. |
| 3 | Do engage respectfully – Comment thoughtfully on posts, share meaningful content, and build a positive digital footprint. |
| 4 | Do showcase your skills – Share your projects, certifications, and learning milestones to build credibility. |
| 5 | Do maintain consistency across platforms – Use the same name, photo, and bio across LinkedIn, GitHub, and Kaggle for a cohesive personal brand. |

---

## ❌ DON'Ts

| # | Don'ts |
|---|--------|
| 1 | Don't post inappropriate content – Avoid photos, comments, or posts that could harm your professional reputation. |
| 2 | Don't engage in arguments – Public debates or negative comments can reflect poorly on your character. |
| 3 | Don't overshare personal information – Keep private details like location, travel plans, and personal conflicts off public platforms. |
| 4 | Don't ignore privacy settings – Regularly review who can see your posts and adjust settings to protect your privacy. |
| 5 | Don't post during class or work hours – Showing that you're distracted or disengaged creates a poor impression. |

